"title": "4912: chance",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "4912",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The occurrence of events at random, as undesigned happenings. While people may perceive events as random, in Scripture all events are subject to God's sovereignty.</p>\n<h2>Chance in human life</h2>\n<h3>Chance events</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr18:33-2Chr18:34\">2CH 18:33–18:34</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs22:34-1Kgs22:38\">1KI 22:34–22:38</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam6:7-1Sam6:9\">1SA 6:7–6:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov26:10\">PRO 26:10</a></p>\n<h3>Human life seems to be governed by chance, not merit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl9:11\">ECC 9:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:17-Eccl2:19\">ECC 2:17–2:19</a></p>\n<h3>Providence at work through apparent chance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah1:17\">JON 1:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth2:3\">RUT 2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:44-Luke23:45\">LUK 23:44–23:45</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:45\">MAT 27:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:51\">MAT 27:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:33\">MRK 15:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:38\">MRK 15:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:26\">ACT 16:26</a></p>\n<h2>Chance events overruled by God's sovereignty</h2>\n<h3>The casting of lots and the element of chance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:33\">PRO 16:33</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num33:53-Num33:54\">NUM 33:53–33:54</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:8-Judg20:10\">JDG 20:8–20:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:34\">NEH 10:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh11:1\">NEH 11:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:34\">LUK 23:34</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:35\">MAT 27:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:24\">MRK 15:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:23-Acts1:26\">ACT 1:23–1:26</a></p>\n<h3>Urim and Thummim, seeming to be dependent on chance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod28:29-Exod28:30\">EXO 28:29–28:30</a></strong> <em>The Urim and Thummim were used by the high priest to declare God's will. It was a form of casting lots showing either an affirmative or negative response to an enquiry.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:21\">NUM 27:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam28:4-1Sam28:6\">1SA 28:4–28:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra2:62-Ezra2:63\">EZR 2:62–2:63</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh7:64-Neh7:65\">NEH 7:64–7:65</a></p>",
